<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span class="title">Worldâs Most Successful Hedge Isnât One <span class="divider">&nbsp;|&nbsp;</span></span><!-- end .title --> George Sorosâs Quantum Endowment Fund was last yearâs most successful hedge fund by dollar gains, but hereâs the catch: Mr. Soros closed Quantum to outside investors at the end of 2011 to avoid regulatory scrutiny. The fund tops the list because it used to be a hedge fund, The Financial Times Alphaville writes, but there are other ways to determine the yearâs top funds.<br /><span class="elsewhere"><a href="//ftalphaville.ft.com/2014/02/10/1767832/the-worlds-most-successful-hedge-fund-is-not-a-hedge-fund/"> FINANCIAL TIMES ALPHAVILLE </a></span></p>
