<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span class="title"> Recent Acquisitions Bolster Britainâs Technology Start-Ups <span class="divider">&nbsp;|&nbsp;</span></span><!-- end .title --> Googleâs purchase of the artificial intelligence company DeepMind last month for 400 million pounds followed by Zyngaâs acquisition of NaturalMotion for $500 million has set Britainâs technology start-up industry abuzz, The Financial Times reports. <br /><span class="elsewhere"><a href="//on.ft.com/1jqEFeL"> FINANCIAL TIMES </a></span></p>
</div>
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><!-- end .ru-story -->
<div class="ru-story">
<p class="story-body-text" itemprop="articleBody"><span class="title">Shazam Expected to Raise $20 Million <span class="divider">&nbsp;|&nbsp;</span></span><!-- end .title --> Shazam, the music discover app, is close to raising $20 million in new funding at a $500 million valuation, ReCode reports, citing unidentified people familiar with the situation.<br /><span class="elsewhere"><a href="//recode.net/2014/02/10/shazam-poised-to-raise-20-million-in-new-funding-at-a-500-million-valuation/"> RECODE </a></span></p>
